dress challenges and barriers to academic success  Set realistic goals and expectations  Understand the various supports available and how to access them  Appropriately refer to U and I Care partners         Eligibility Requirements:         COntent    Maintain a minimum of 2.75 GPA  No disciplinary record with the Office of the Dean of Students  Completed 45 credit hours or more  Received a grade of B or higher in PSCH 386: Crisis Techniques I              Want to join the team?     Application Process   For full consideration, applications are due November 15th. Selected candidates are notified and invited to participate in interviews in late November/early December. Interested candidates must submit their resume and one letter of recommendation along with their application. If selected, training will begin in early January.     Apply Now!   Applications are available to students who have completed PSCH 386 or are currently enrolled in PSCH 386. Students can find the application here: APPLY TODAY!               Assistance    Back to main content           Academic Concerns     Academic Resources    Academic Grievances    Withdrawal    Emergencies and Absences      Health & Personal Concerns     Hospitalization & Emergencies    Mental Health    Victims of Crime and Safety Concerns    Housing Instability & Food Insecurity    Financial Concerns    Cannabis: Know the Facts      Campus Life    Faculty & Staff Resources     The Student Response Team    Behavioral Response Intervention Team      U & I Care     Meet Our Partners    Care Facts    News & Events    U & I Care Fund    U & I Care Plan                    UIC Logo        Office of the Dean of Students         DOS Offices    Career Services    Student Employment    Counseling Center    Wellness Center      For Employees    SA Human Resources    SA Technology    Leave Management    The Pulse      Safety    UIC Police    Office of Access & Equity    Contact-US    Giving         Contact   1200 West Harrison St., 303